layers%20have%20a%20scoring%20hand%2C%20the%20higher%20hand%20wins%20the%20round.%20Ranking%2C%20high%20to%20low%3A%20%3Cstrong%3E4-5-6%20%E2%86%92%20trips%20%E2%86%92%20point%20%E2%86%92%201-2-3%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Ties%20push%20and%20the%20round%20is%20replayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20to%20%3Cstrong%3E3%20round%20wins%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20takes%20the%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22history%22%3EHistory%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECee-lo%20(also%20%E2%80%9Csee-low%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CC-Lo%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20half-dozen%20other%20spellings)%20is%20a%20street%20and%20bar%20dice%20game%20with%20roots%20in%2019th-century%20Chinese%20gambling%2C%20popularized%20in%20the%20US%20through%20the%20early-1900s%20gambling%20halls%20and%20lasting%20into%20modern%20hip-hop%20culture%20-%20it%20shows%20up%20in%20songs%20by%20Wu-Tang%20Clan%2C%20Jay-Z%2C%20and%20others.%20The%20name%20is%20a%20corruption%20of%20the%20Cantonese%20%E7%B4%B0%E8%B7%AF%20(%E2%80%9Csee%20lo%E2%80%9D)%2C%20variously%20rendered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20dozens%20of%20regional%20variants%20-%20%E2%80%9Cbank%E2%80%9D%20cee-lo%20with%20a%20permanent%20banker%2C%20%E2%80%9Cchasing%20the%20ace%2C%E2%80%9D%20doubles-only%20scoring%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20version%20here%20is%20the%20most%20common%201-vs-1%20form%3A%20simple%20ranking%2C%20ties%20replay%2C%20no%20betting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20strategy%3A%20you%20roll%20until%20the%20dice%20tell%20you%20the%20answer.%20The%20fun%20is%20the%20volatility%20-%204-5-6%20and%201-2-3%20are%20both%201-in-36%20per%20roll%2C%20so%20swings%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22references%22%3EReferences%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FCee-lo%22%3ECee-lo%3C%2Fa%3E%20-%20Wikipedia%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cmain%20id%3D%22stage%22%3E%3Ccanvas%20data-engine%3D%22three.js%20r177%22%20width%3D%221280%22%20height%3D%22720%22%20style%3D%22display%3A%20block%3B%20width%3A%201280px%3B%20height